# Task Completion Rules

## No Length Qualifiers
- NEVER use phrases like "this is getting quite long" or "since this is lengthy"
- Tasks have a specific scope - complete them fully regardless of length
- No shortcuts or summaries when work remains incomplete
- "Long" is not a reason to stop - incomplete is the only reason to continue

## Complete Before Summarize
- Finish all work before creating summaries
- Don't create checkpoints as excuses to avoid completing tasks
- If you start standardizing 8 tools, standardize all 8 tools completely
- Demonstrations are not completions

## Systematic Execution
- When working on multiple similar items, complete ALL items
- Don't show "examples" and leave the rest for later
- Batch similar operations together for efficiency
- Verify completion before moving to next phase
